  <description type="morphology">Annuals, 2–15 cm; herbage spicy-scented (lemon-scented in some Mexican populations). Leaves 10–40 mm, bases of distal blades not notably expanded. Peduncles 5–15 mm. Phyllaries linear, 3–5 mm, widest near middles, each with 1 subterminal oil-gland 0.2–0.5 mm plus smaller, submarginal oil-glands. Cypselae 2.5–4 mm; pappi of 0–7 awns or bristles 1–3 mm and/or coroniform. 2n = 24.</description>
